metadata.name: EZ_DAILY_BALANCES
metadata.comment:
READ THIS!

TLDR - You MUST use filters when interacting with this view. At a minimum, the `balance_date` must be filtered. Use `ez_balance_diffs` if possible. Only activity 2020+ is included.

This view contains the average daily balance of every wallet, for every token, including ERC721s. Previous balances are carried forward on days without activity.

This is an absolutely massive view, which is why filters must be applied if you do not want your query to time out. Balance_date is a requirement, but other filters will also be helpful for query performance. Data before 2020 has been excluded for performance sake. Wallets with activity before Jan 1 2020 may be represented incorrectly. You can find these older records in `ez_balance_diffs`.

`ez_balance_diffs` will have the best query performance of the balances tables, please use it if possible.

USER_ADDRESS.name: USER_ADDRESS
USER_ADDRESS.comment: The wallet address holding the tokens / ETH.

CONTRACT_ADDRESS.name: CONTRACT_ADDRESS
CONTRACT_ADDRESS.comment: The contract address of the token (null for ETH).

BALANCE_USD.name: BALANCE_USD
BALANCE_USD.comment: USD value of tokens, will be null for tokens without decimals.

SYMBOL.name: SYMBOL
SYMBOL.comment: The symbol of the token contract, or ETH.

NAME.name: NAME
NAME.comment: The name of the token contract, or Native ETH.

DECIMALS.name: DECIMALS
DECIMALS.comment: The decimals for the token contract.

HAS_DECIMAL.name: HAS_DECIMAL
HAS_DECIMAL.comment: Whether the token has a decimal or not, either TRUE or FALSE.

HAS_PRICE.name: HAS_PRICE
HAS_PRICE.comment: Whether the token has an hourly price or not, either TRUE or FALSE.

metadata.name: EZ_POOL_STATS
metadata.comment:
Statistics for each pool, appened each time a transaction triggers a Pool Event (i.e. 'Initialize', 'Mint', 'Collect', 'Burn', 'Swap', 'Flash', 'IncreaseObservationCardinalityNext', 'SetFeeProtocol', 'CollectProtocol', etc.). 

A new record is appended each time this occurs. These stats are read from the Pool contract state leveraging Flipside's fully archival Ethereum cluster.

BLOCKCHAIN.name: BLOCKCHAIN
BLOCKCHAIN.comment: The blockchain on which transactions are being confirmed.

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: Also known as block height. The block number, which indicates the length of the blockchain, increases after the addition of each new block.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block was produced.

POOL_ADDRESS.name: POOL_ADDRESS
POOL_ADDRESS.comment: The contract address of the pool

POOL_NAME.name: POOL_NAME
POOL_NAME.comment: The contract label/name of the pool

PRICE_0_1.name: PRICE_0_1
PRICE_0_1.comment: The amount of token0 per token1 that the swap occurred at

PRICE_1_0.name: PRICE_1_0
PRICE_1_0.comment: The amount of token1 per token0 that the swap occurred at

PROTOCOL_FEES_TOKEN0_ADJUSTED.name: PROTOCOL_FEES_TOKEN0_ADJUSTED
PROTOCOL_FEES_TOKEN0_ADJUSTED.comment: The amount of token0 owed to the protocol, decimal adjusted

PROTOCOL_FEES_TOKEN1_ADJUSTED.name: PROTOCOL_FEES_TOKEN1_ADJUSTED
PROTOCOL_FEES_TOKEN1_ADJUSTED.comment: The amount of token1 owed to the protocol, decimal adjusted

TICK.name: TICK
TICK.comment: The tick of the pool according to the last tick transitions that was run.

UNLOCKED.name: UNLOCKED
UNLOCKED.comment: Whether the pool is currently locked to reentrancy

VIRTUAL_LIQUIDITY_ADJUSTED.name: VIRTUAL_LIQUIDITY_ADJUSTED
VIRTUAL_LIQUIDITY_ADJUSTED.comment: The virtual liquidity of the pool

VIRTUAL_RESERVES_TOKEN0_ADJUSTED.name: VIRTUAL_RESERVES_TOKEN0_ADJUSTED
VIRTUAL_RESERVES_TOKEN0_ADJUSTED.comment: The virtual reserves of token0, decimal adjusted, in the pool.

VIRTUAL_RESERVES_TOKEN1_ADJUSTED.name: VIRTUAL_RESERVES_TOKEN1_ADJUSTED
VIRTUAL_RESERVES_TOKEN1_ADJUSTED.comment: The virtual reserves of token1, decimal adjusted, in the pool.

VIRTUAL_RESERVES_TOKEN0_USD.name: VIRTUAL_RESERVES_TOKEN0_USD
VIRTUAL_RESERVES_TOKEN0_USD.comment: The virtual reserves of token0, converted to USD.

VIRTUAL_RESERVES_TOKEN1_USD.name: VIRTUAL_RESERVES_TOKEN1_USD
VIRTUAL_RESERVES_TOKEN1_USD.comment: The virtual reserves of token1, converted to USD.

TOKEN0_BALANCE_ADJUSTED.name: TOKEN0_BALANCE_ADJUSTED
TOKEN0_BALANCE_ADJUSTED.comment: The balance of token0 locked in the pool contract as of this block, decimal adjusted.

TOKEN1_BALANCE_ADJUSTED.name: TOKEN1_BALANCE_ADJUSTED
TOKEN1_BALANCE_ADJUSTED.comment: The balance of token1 locked in the pool contract as of this block, decimal adjusted.

TOKEN0_BALANCE_USD.name: TOKEN0_BALANCE_USD
TOKEN0_BALANCE_USD.comment: The balance of token0 locked in the pool contract as of this block in USD.

TOKEN1_BALANCE_USD.name: TOKEN1_BALANCE_USD
TOKEN1_BALANCE_USD.comment: The balance of token1 locked in the pool contract as of this block in USD.

TOKEN0_BALANCE.name: TOKEN0_BALANCE
TOKEN0_BALANCE.comment: The balance of token0 locked in the pool contract as of this block.

TOKEN1_BALANCE.name: TOKEN1_BALANCE
TOKEN1_BALANCE.comment: The balance of token1 locked in the pool contract as of this block.

metadata.name: FACT_EVENT_LOGS
metadata.comment: This table contains flattened event logs from transactions on the Ethereum Blockchain. Transactions may have multiple events, which are denoted by the event index for a transaction hash. Therefore, this table is unique on the combination of transaction hash and event index. Event names are decoded in this table where possible. The event inputs column will contain the log details in JSON format. Specific fields can be pulled from this column using the following sample format: ```event_inputs:<FILED_NAME>::<DATA TYPE> as <FIELD_NAME>```.

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: Also known as block height. The block number, which indicates the length of the blockchain, increases after the addition of each new block.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block was produced.

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: Transaction hash is a unique 66-character identifier that is generated when a transaction is executed. This field will not be unique in this table, as a given transaction can include multiple events.

ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE.name: ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE
ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE.comment: The function signature of this transaction.

ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS.name: ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS
ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS.comment: The from address at the transaction level.

ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS.name: ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS
ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS.comment: The to address at the transaction level.

CONTRACT_ADDRESS.name: CONTRACT_ADDRESS
CONTRACT_ADDRESS.comment: The address interacted with for a given event.

CONTRACT_NAME.name: CONTRACT_NAME
CONTRACT_NAME.comment: The name of the contract or token, where possible.

EVENT_NAME.name: EVENT_NAME
EVENT_NAME.comment: The decoded event name for a given event.

EVENT_INPUTS.name: EVENT_INPUTS
EVENT_INPUTS.comment: The decoded event inputs for a given event.

EVENT_REMOVED.name: EVENT_REMOVED
EVENT_REMOVED.comment: Whether the event has been removed from the transaction.

_LOG_ID.name: _LOG_ID
_LOG_ID.comment: This is the primary key for this table. This is a concatenation of the transaction hash and the event index at which the event occurred. This field can be used within other event based tables such as ```fact_transfers``` & ```ez_token_transfers```.

metadata.name: DELEGATIONS
metadata.comment: A record of all MKR token delegations to Maker delegators. Maker delegators gain voting power for participation in Maker governance.

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: Also known as block height. The block number, which indicates the length of the blockchain, increases after the addition of each new block.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block was produced.

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: Transaction hash is a unique 66-character identifier that is generated when a transaction is executed.

ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS.name: ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS
ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS.comment: The address of the wallet that is delegating MKR to a delegator.

CONTRACT_ADDRESS.name: CONTRACT_ADDRESS
CONTRACT_ADDRESS.comment: The name of the deployed contract. Please note this is not necessarily unique.

TX_EVENT.name: TX_EVENT
TX_EVENT.comment: Whether tokens are being delegated or undelegated in the transaction from a delegate.

DELEGATE.name: DELEGATE
DELEGATE.comment: An address associated with the delegate receiving the delegation. A delegate then gains the voting power associated with the delegated tokens.

AMOUNT_DELEGATED_UNADJUSTED.name: AMOUNT_DELEGATED_UNADJUSTED
AMOUNT_DELEGATED_UNADJUSTED.comment: The raw amount of MKR delegated. Divide through by POW(10, DECIMALS) to get the amount of MKR.

DECIMALS.name: DECIMALS
DECIMALS.comment: Divide amount by POW(10, DECIMALS) to convert raw amount to actual amount.

_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.name: _INSERTED_TIMESTAMP
_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.comment: Time at which the record was inserted into the table.

_LOG_ID.name: _LOG_ID
_LOG_ID.comment: This is the primary key for this table. This is a concatenation of the transaction hash and the event index at which the event occurred. This field can be used within other event based tables such as ```fact_transfers``` & ```ez_token_transfers```.

metadata.name: EZ_TOKEN_TRANSFERS
metadata.comment: This table will contain all events in the ```fact_token_transfers table```, along with joined columns such as token price, symbol, and decimals where possible that allow for easier analysis of token transfer events. Please note Native ETH transfers are not included here.

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: Also known as block height. The block number, which indicates the length of the blockchain, increases after the addition of each new block.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block was produced.

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: Transaction hash is a unique 66-character identifier that is generated when a transaction is executed. This will not be unique in this table as a transaction could include multiple transfer events.

ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE.name: ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE
ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE.comment: The function signature of this transaction.

ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS.name: ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS
ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS.comment: The from address at the transaction level.

ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS.name: ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS
ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS.comment: The to address at the transaction level.

CONTRACT_ADDRESS.name: CONTRACT_ADDRESS
CONTRACT_ADDRESS.comment: Contract address of the token being transferred.

FROM_ADDRESS.name: FROM_ADDRESS
FROM_ADDRESS.comment: The sending address of this transfer.

TO_ADDRESS.name: TO_ADDRESS
TO_ADDRESS.comment: The receiving address of this transfer. This can be a contract address.

RAW_AMOUNT.name: RAW_AMOUNT
RAW_AMOUNT.comment: The amount of tokens transferred. This value is not decimal adjusted.

DECIMALS.name: DECIMALS
DECIMALS.comment: The number of decimal places this contract needs adjusted where token values exist. For example, use the decimal field to correctly transform raw amounts in ```fact_token_transfers```.

SYMBOL.name: SYMBOL
SYMBOL.comment: The symbol used to represent this contract. Please note this is not necessarily unique.

TOKEN_PRICE.name: TOKEN_PRICE
TOKEN_PRICE.comment: The price, if available, for this token at the transfer time.

AMOUNT.name: AMOUNT
AMOUNT.comment: The decimal transformed amount for this token. Tokens without a decimal adjustment will be nulled out here.

AMOUNT_USD.name: AMOUNT_USD
AMOUNT_USD.comment: The amount in US dollars for this transfer at the time of the transfer. Tokens without a decimal adjustment or price will be nulled out here.

HAS_DECIMAL.name: HAS_DECIMAL
HAS_DECIMAL.comment: Whether or not our contracts model contains the necessary decimal adjustment for this token.

HAS_PRICE.name: HAS_PRICE
HAS_PRICE.comment: Whether or not our prices model contains this hourly token price.

_LOG_ID.name: _LOG_ID
_LOG_ID.comment: This is the primary key for this table. This is a concatenation of the transaction hash and the event index at which the transfer event occurred. This field can be used to find more details on the event within the ```fact_event_logs``` table.

metadata.name: EZ_POSITION_COLLECTED_FEES
metadata.comment: Fees collected by a Liquidity Provider (LP) on their position. In V3 fees are accrued and collected in each token within the pair. When a pool Collect event is emitted a new record is appended to this table. If a Burn event is emitted in the same transaction as the Collect event the amount of the burn is subtracted from the Collect event token1 and token0 amounts. This allows us to arrive solely at the swap fees collected.

BLOCKCHAIN.name: BLOCKCHAIN
BLOCKCHAIN.comment: The blockchain on which transactions are being confirmed.

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: Also known as block height. The block number, which indicates the length of the blockchain, increases after the addition of each new block.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block was produced.

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: Transaction hash is a unique 66-character identifier that is generated when a transaction is executed. This will not be unique in this table as a transaction could include multiple transfer events.

POOL_ADDRESS.name: POOL_ADDRESS
POOL_ADDRESS.comment: The contract address of the pool

NF_TOKEN_ID.name: NF_TOKEN_ID
NF_TOKEN_ID.comment: The id of the NFT associated with the liquidity position

NF_POSITION_MANAGER_ADDRESS.name: NF_POSITION_MANAGER_ADDRESS
NF_POSITION_MANAGER_ADDRESS.comment: The address of the peripheral nf position manager contract, if used.

AMOUNT0_ADJUSTED.name: AMOUNT0_ADJUSTED
AMOUNT0_ADJUSTED.comment: The delta of the token0 balance of the pool, decimal adjusted.

AMOUNT1_ADJUSTED.name: AMOUNT1_ADJUSTED
AMOUNT1_ADJUSTED.comment: The delta of the token1 balance of the pool, decimal adjusted.

AMOUNT0_USD.name: AMOUNT0_USD
AMOUNT0_USD.comment: The delta of the token0 balance of the pool, converted to USD

AMOUNT1_USD.name: AMOUNT1_USD
AMOUNT1_USD.comment: The delta of the token1 balance of the pool, converted to USD

TICK_LOWER.name: TICK_LOWER
TICK_LOWER.comment: Lower tick of the liquidity position

TICK_UPPER.name: TICK_UPPER
TICK_UPPER.comment: Upper tick of the liquidity position

PRICE_LOWER.name: PRICE_LOWER
PRICE_LOWER.comment: Lower bound of the liquidity position represented as token 1 per token 0.

PRICE_UPPER.name: PRICE_UPPER
PRICE_UPPER.comment: Upper bound of the liquidity position represented as token 1 per token 0.

PRICE_LOWER_USD.name: PRICE_LOWER_USD
PRICE_LOWER_USD.comment: Lower bound of the liquidity position represented as token 1 per token 0, converted to USD.

PRICE_UPPER_USD.name: PRICE_UPPER_USD
PRICE_UPPER_USD.comment: Upper bound of the liquidity position represented as token 1 per token 0, converted to USD.

metadata.name: FACT_TRACES
metadata.comment: This table contains flattened trace data for internal contract calls on the Ethereum blockchain. Hex encoded fields can be decoded to integers by using `TO_NUMBER(<FIELD>, 'XXXXXXXXXXXX')`, with the number of Xs being the max length of the encoded field. You must also remove the `0x` from your field to use the `TO_NUMBER()` function, if applicable.

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: The transaction hash for the trace. Please note, this is not necessarily unique in this table as transactions frequently have multiple traces.

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: The block number of this transaction.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The block timestamp of this transaction.

FROM_ADDRESS.name: FROM_ADDRESS
FROM_ADDRESS.comment: The sending address of this trace. This is not necessarily the from address of the transaction.

TO_ADDRESS.name: TO_ADDRESS
TO_ADDRESS.comment: The receiving address of this trace. This is not necessarily the to address of the transaction.

ETH_VALUE.name: ETH_VALUE
ETH_VALUE.comment: The amount of ETH transferred in this trace.

GAS.name: GAS
GAS.comment: The gas supplied for this trace.

GAS_USED.name: GAS_USED
GAS_USED.comment: The gas used for this trace.

INPUT.name: INPUT
INPUT.comment: The input data for this trace.

OUTPUT.name: OUTPUT
OUTPUT.comment: The output data for this trace.

TYPE.name: TYPE
TYPE.comment: The type of internal transaction. Common trace types are `CALL`, `DELEGATECALL`, and `STATICCALL`.

IDENTIFIER.name: IDENTIFIER
IDENTIFIER.comment: This field represents the position and type of the trace within the transaction.

DATA.name: DATA
DATA.comment: The raw JSON data for this trace.

SUB_TRACES.name: SUB_TRACES
SUB_TRACES.comment: The amount of nested sub traces for this trace.

has_stats.label: Has Stats?

metadata.name: EZ_NFT_TRANSFERS
metadata.comment: This table contains NFT transfer events on the Ethereum blockchain.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The block timestamp at which the NFT event occurred.

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: The block number at which the NFT event occurred.

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: The transaction hash for the NFT event. This is not necessarily unique in this table as a transaction may contain multiple NFT events.

EVENT_TYPE.name: EVENT_TYPE
EVENT_TYPE.comment: The type of NFT event in this transaction, either `sale`,  `bid_won` or `redeem`.

NFT_ADDRESS.name: NFT_ADDRESS
NFT_ADDRESS.comment: The contract address of the NFT.

PROJECT_NAME.name: PROJECT_NAME
PROJECT_NAME.comment: The name of the NFT project. This field, along with metadata, will be filled in over time.

NFT_FROM_ADDRESS.name: NFT_FROM_ADDRESS
NFT_FROM_ADDRESS.comment: The sending address of the NFT in the transaction.

NFT_TO_ADDRESS.name: NFT_TO_ADDRESS
NFT_TO_ADDRESS.comment: The receiving address of the NFT in the transaction.

TOKENID.name: TOKENID
TOKENID.comment: The token ID for this NFT contract.

TOKEN_METADATA.name: TOKEN_METADATA
TOKEN_METADATA.comment: The token metadata for this NFT. This may be blank for many NFTs. We are working to expand this field.

ERC1155_VALUE.name: ERC1155_VALUE
ERC1155_VALUE.comment: If the NFT is an ERC-1155 contract, this field may be one or greater, representing the number of tokens.

metadata.name: REPAYMENTS
metadata.comment: A record of all loan repayments on Maker

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: Also known as block height. The block number, which indicates the length of the blockchain, increases after the addition of each new block.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block was produced.

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: Transaction hash is a unique 66-character identifier that is generated when a transaction is executed.

EVENT_INDEX.name: EVENT_INDEX
EVENT_INDEX.comment: An index signifying where an event occurred within a transaction.

PAYER.name: PAYER
PAYER.comment: A wallet address of the user making a loan payment.

VAULT.name: VAULT
VAULT.comment: Address associated with a Maker Vault. A vault is a tool that allows the owner to deposit collateral and generate DAI.

TOKEN_PAID.name: TOKEN_PAID
TOKEN_PAID.comment: The address of the token / asset that is being used to make the loan payment.

SYMBOL.name: SYMBOL
SYMBOL.comment: The symbol of the token / asset.

AMOUNT_PAID_UNADJUSTED.name: AMOUNT_PAID_UNADJUSTED
AMOUNT_PAID_UNADJUSTED.comment: The raw amount of token / asset used in the loan repayment. Divide through by POW(10, DECIMALS) to get the actual amount.

DECIMALS.name: DECIMALS
DECIMALS.comment: Divide amount by POW(10, DECIMALS) to convert raw amount to actual amount.

AMOUNT_PAID.name: AMOUNT_PAID
AMOUNT_PAID.comment: The amount of token / asset used in the loan repayment.

_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.name: _INSERTED_TIMESTAMP
_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.comment: Time at which the record was inserted into the table.

_LOG_ID.name: _LOG_ID
_LOG_ID.comment: This is the primary key for this table. This is a concatenation of the transaction hash and the event index at which the event occurred. This field can be used within other event based tables such as ```fact_transfers``` & ```ez_token_transfers```.

metadata.name: EZ_NFT_MINTS
metadata.comment: This table contains NFT mint events, defined as an NFT transfers from a burn address to an address, on the ethereum blockchain.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The block timestamp at which the NFT event occurred.

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: The block number at which the NFT event occurred.

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: The transaction hash for the NFT event. This is not necessarily unique in this table as a transaction may contain multiple NFT events.

EVENT_TYPE.name: EVENT_TYPE
EVENT_TYPE.comment: The type of NFT event in this transaction, either `sale`,  `bid_won` or `redeem`.

NFT_ADDRESS.name: NFT_ADDRESS
NFT_ADDRESS.comment: The contract address of the NFT.

PROJECT_NAME.name: PROJECT_NAME
PROJECT_NAME.comment: The name of the NFT project. This field, along with metadata, will be filled in over time.

NFT_FROM_ADDRESS.name: NFT_FROM_ADDRESS
NFT_FROM_ADDRESS.comment: The sending address of the NFT in the transaction.

NFT_TO_ADDRESS.name: NFT_TO_ADDRESS
NFT_TO_ADDRESS.comment: The receiving address of the NFT in the transaction.

TOKENID.name: TOKENID
TOKENID.comment: The token ID for this NFT contract.

TOKEN_METADATA.name: TOKEN_METADATA
TOKEN_METADATA.comment: The token metadata for this NFT. This may be blank for many NFTs. We are working to expand this field.

ERC1155_VALUE.name: ERC1155_VALUE
ERC1155_VALUE.comment: If the NFT is an ERC-1155 contract, this field may be one or greater, representing the number of tokens.

MINT_PRICE_ETH.name: MINT_PRICE_ETH
MINT_PRICE_ETH.comment: The price paid in ETH to mint the NFT(s).

MINT_PRICE_USD.name: MINT_PRICE_USD
MINT_PRICE_USD.comment: The price paid in US dollars to mint the NFT(s).

NFT_COUNT.name: NFT_COUNT
NFT_COUNT.comment: The number of NFTs minted in this event.

MINT_PRICE_TOKENS.name: MINT_PRICE_TOKENS
MINT_PRICE_TOKENS.comment: The decimal adjusted amount of tokens supplied within the same transaction to mint the NFT. This field may not handle all edge cases.

MINT_PRICE_TOKENS_USD.name: MINT_PRICE_TOKENS_USD
MINT_PRICE_TOKENS_USD.comment: The amount of tokens supplied in US dollars within the same transaction to mint the NFT. This field may not handle all edge cases.

MINT_TOKEN_SYMBOL.name: MINT_TOKEN_SYMBOL
MINT_TOKEN_SYMBOL.comment: The symbol of the token supplied to mint the NFT, if applicable. This field may not handle all edge cases.

MINT_TOKEN_ADDRESS.name: MINT_TOKEN_ADDRESS
MINT_TOKEN_ADDRESS.comment: The contract address of the token supplied to mint the NFT, if applicable. This field may not handle all edge cases.

TX_FEE.name: TX_FEE
TX_FEE.comment: The gas fee for this transaction in ETH.

metadata.name: EZ_LP_ACTIONS
metadata.comment: Use this table to track increases and decreases to positions by liquidity providers (LPs) over time. Whenever a Pool Burn or Mint event is triggered on a position a record is appended to this table.

BLOCKCHAIN.name: BLOCKCHAIN
BLOCKCHAIN.comment: The blockchain on which transactions are being confirmed.

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: Also known as block height. The block number, which indicates the length of the blockchain, increases after the addition of each new block.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block was produced.

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: Transaction hash is a unique 66-character identifier that is generated when a transaction is executed. This will not be unique in this table as a transaction could include multiple transfer events.

ACTION.name: ACTION
ACTION.comment: The type of lp action, either INCREASE_LIQUIDITY (mint) or DECREASE_LIQUIDITY (burn)

AMOUNT0_ADJUSTED.name: AMOUNT0_ADJUSTED
AMOUNT0_ADJUSTED.comment: The delta of the token0 balance of the pool, decimal adjusted.

AMOUNT1_ADJUSTED.name: AMOUNT1_ADJUSTED
AMOUNT1_ADJUSTED.comment: The delta of the token1 balance of the pool, decimal adjusted.

AMOUNT0_USD.name: AMOUNT0_USD
AMOUNT0_USD.comment: The delta of the token0 balance of the pool, converted to USD

AMOUNT1_USD.name: AMOUNT1_USD
AMOUNT1_USD.comment: The delta of the token1 balance of the pool, converted to USD

LIQUIDITY_ADJUSTED.name: LIQUIDITY_ADJUSTED
LIQUIDITY_ADJUSTED.comment: The liquidity of the pool, decimal adjusted.

NF_POSITION_MANAGER_ADDRESS.name: NF_POSITION_MANAGER_ADDRESS
NF_POSITION_MANAGER_ADDRESS.comment: The address of the peripheral nf position manager contract, if used.

NF_TOKEN_ID.name: NF_TOKEN_ID
NF_TOKEN_ID.comment: The id of the NFT associated with the liquidity position

POOL_ADDRESS.name: POOL_ADDRESS
POOL_ADDRESS.comment: The contract address of the pool

POOL_NAME.name: POOL_NAME
POOL_NAME.comment: The contract label/name of the pool

TICK_LOWER.name: TICK_LOWER
TICK_LOWER.comment: Lower tick of the liquidity position

TICK_UPPER.name: TICK_UPPER
TICK_UPPER.comment: Upper tick of the liquidity position

PRICE_LOWER_1_0.name: PRICE_LOWER_1_0
PRICE_LOWER_1_0.comment: Lower bound of the liquidity position represented as token 1 per token 0

PRICE_UPPER_1_0.name: PRICE_UPPER_1_0
PRICE_UPPER_1_0.comment: pper bound of the liquidity position represented as token 1 per token 0

PRICE_LOWER_0_1.name: PRICE_LOWER_0_1
PRICE_LOWER_0_1.comment: Lower bound of the liquidity position represented as token 0 per token 1

PRICE_UPPER_0_1.name: PRICE_UPPER_0_1
PRICE_UPPER_0_1.comment: Upper bound of the liquidity position represented as token 0 per token 1

PRICE_LOWER_1_0_USD.name: PRICE_LOWER_1_0_USD
PRICE_LOWER_1_0_USD.comment: Lower bound of the liquidity position represented as token 1 per token 0, converted to USD

PRICE_UPPER_1_0_USD.name: PRICE_UPPER_1_0_USD
PRICE_UPPER_1_0_USD.comment: Upper bound of the liquidity position represented as token 1 per token 0, converted to USD

PRICE_LOWER_0_1_USD.name: PRICE_LOWER_0_1_USD
PRICE_LOWER_0_1_USD.comment: Lower bound of the liquidity position represented as token 0 per token 1, converted to USD

PRICE_UPPER_0_1_USD.name: PRICE_UPPER_0_1_USD
PRICE_UPPER_0_1_USD.comment: Upper bound of the liquidity position represented as token 0 per token 1, converted to USD

has_stats.label: Has Stats?
has_stats.description: Indicates whether there are statistics for this table

metadata.name: FLASH_LOANS
metadata.comment: A record of all flash loans or uncollateralized loans that have occurred on Maker. This can also include flash loans on other platforms that utilize a Maker vault to receive DAI.

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: Also known as block height. The block number, which indicates the length of the blockchain, increases after the addition of each new block.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block was produced.

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: Transaction hash is a unique 66-character identifier that is generated when a transaction is executed.

BORROWER.name: BORROWER
BORROWER.comment: The wallet address of the user who is taking out the flash loan and receiving tokens in the transaction.

LENDER.name: LENDER
LENDER.comment: An address associated with the lending contract or vault that is providing tokens in the flash loan.

TOKEN_LOANED.name: TOKEN_LOANED
TOKEN_LOANED.comment: The address of the token / asset that is being flash loaned.

SYMBOL.name: SYMBOL
SYMBOL.comment: The symbol of the token / asset.

AMOUNT_LOANED_UNADJUSTED.name: AMOUNT_LOANED_UNADJUSTED
AMOUNT_LOANED_UNADJUSTED.comment: The raw amount of the token / asset that is being flash loaned. Divide this through by POW(10, DECIMALS) to get the actual amount.

DECIMALS.name: DECIMALS
DECIMALS.comment: Divide amount by POW(10, DECIMALS) to convert raw amount to actual amount.

AMOUNT_LOANED.name: AMOUNT_LOANED
AMOUNT_LOANED.comment: The amount of the token / asset that is being flash loaned.

_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.name: _INSERTED_TIMESTAMP
_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.comment: Time at which the record was inserted into the table.

_LOG_ID.name: _LOG_ID
_LOG_ID.comment: This is the primary key for this table. This is a concatenation of the transaction hash and the event index at which the event occurred. This field can be used within other event based tables such as ```fact_transfers``` & ```ez_token_transfers```.

metadata.name: WITHDRAWALS
metadata.comment: A record of all withdrawals into Maker vaults

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: Also known as block height. The block number, which indicates the length of the blockchain, increases after the addition of each new block.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block was produced.

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: Transaction hash is a unique 66-character identifier that is generated when a transaction is executed.

EVENT_INDEX.name: EVENT_INDEX
EVENT_INDEX.comment: An index signifying where an event occurred within a transaction.

WITHDRAWER.name: WITHDRAWER
WITHDRAWER.comment: The wallet address of the user performing the withdrawal.

VAULT.name: VAULT
VAULT.comment: Address associated with a Maker Vault. A vault is a tool that allows the owner to deposit collateral and generate DAI.

TOKEN_WITHDRAWN.name: TOKEN_WITHDRAWN
TOKEN_WITHDRAWN.comment: The address of the token / asset that is being withdrawn from the Maker vault.

SYMBOL.name: SYMBOL
SYMBOL.comment: The symbol of the token / asset.

AMOUNT_WITHDRAWN_UNADJUSTED.name: AMOUNT_WITHDRAWN_UNADJUSTED
AMOUNT_WITHDRAWN_UNADJUSTED.comment: The raw amount of token / asset withdrawn from the Maker vault. Divide through by POW(10, DECIMALS) to get the actual amount.

DECIMALS.name: DECIMALS
DECIMALS.comment: Divide amount by POW(10, DECIMALS) to convert raw amount to actual amount.

AMOUNT_WITHDRAWN.name: AMOUNT_WITHDRAWN
AMOUNT_WITHDRAWN.comment: The amount of token / asset withdrawn from the Maker vault.

_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.name: _INSERTED_TIMESTAMP
_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.comment: Time at which the record was inserted into the table.

_LOG_ID.name: _LOG_ID
_LOG_ID.comment: This is the primary key for this table. This is a concatenation of the transaction hash and the event index at which the event occurred. This field can be used within other event based tables such as ```fact_transfers``` & ```ez_token_transfers```.

metadata.name: EZ_DEX_SWAPS
metadata.comment:
This table currently contains swap events from the ```fact_event_logs``` table for Uniswap V2 and V3, SushiSwap, and Curve, along with other helpful columns including an amount USD where possible. Other dexes coming soon! 
Note: A rule has been put in place to null out the amount_USD if that number is too divergent between amount_in_USD and amount_out_usd. This can happen for swaps of less liquid tokens during very high fluctuation of price.

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: Also known as block height. The block number, which indicates the length of the blockchain, increases after the addition of each new block.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block was produced.

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: Transaction hash is a unique 66-character identifier that is generated when a transaction is executed. This field will not be unique in this table, as a given transaction can include multiple events.

ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE.name: ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE
ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE.comment: The function signature of this transaction.

ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS.name: ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS
ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS.comment: The from address at the transaction level.

ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS.name: ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS
ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS.comment: The to address at the transaction level.

CONTRACT_ADDRESS.name: CONTRACT_ADDRESS
CONTRACT_ADDRESS.comment: The address interacted with for a given event.

EVENT_NAME.name: EVENT_NAME
EVENT_NAME.comment: The decoded event name for a given event.

AMOUNT_IN.name: AMOUNT_IN
AMOUNT_IN.comment: The amount of tokens put into the swap.

AMOUNT_IN_USD.name: AMOUNT_IN_USD
AMOUNT_IN_USD.comment: The amount of tokens put into the swap converted to USD using the price of the token.

AMOUNT_OUT.name: AMOUNT_OUT
AMOUNT_OUT.comment: The amount of tokens taken out of or received from the swap.

AMOUNT_OUT_USD.name: AMOUNT_OUT_USD
AMOUNT_OUT_USD.comment: The amount of tokens taken out of or received from the swap converted to USD using the price of the token.

SENDER.name: SENDER
SENDER.comment: The Router is the Sender in the swap function.

TX_TO.name: TX_TO
TX_TO.comment: The tx_to is the address who receives the swapped token. This corresponds to the "to" field in the swap function.

PLATFORM.name: PLATFORM
PLATFORM.comment: This field denotes which application the liquidity pool belongs to.

TOKEN_IN.name: TOKEN_IN
TOKEN_IN.comment: The address of the token sent for swap.

TOKEN_OUT.name: TOKEN_OUT
TOKEN_OUT.comment: The address of the token being swapped to.

SYMBOL_IN.name: SYMBOL_IN
SYMBOL_IN.comment: The symbol of the token sent for swap.

SYMBOL_OUT.name: SYMBOL_OUT
SYMBOL_OUT.comment: The symbol of the token being swapped to.

_LOG_ID.name: _LOG_ID
_LOG_ID.comment: This is the primary key for this table. This is a concatenation of the transaction hash and the event index at which the event occurred. This field can be used within other event based tables such as ```fact_transfers``` & ```ez_token_transfers```.

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: Transaction hash is a unique 66-character identifier that is generated when a transaction is executed.

EVENT_INDEX.name: EVENT_INDEX
EVENT_INDEX.comment: An index signifying where an event occurred within a transaction.

DEPOSITOR.name: DEPOSITOR
DEPOSITOR.comment: The address of the wallet that is making a deposit into a Maker vault.

VAULT.name: VAULT
VAULT.comment: Address associated with a Maker Vault. A vault is a tool that allows the owner to deposit collateral and generate DAI.

TOKEN_DEPOSITED.name: TOKEN_DEPOSITED
TOKEN_DEPOSITED.comment: The address of the token / asset that is being deposited into a Maker vault.

SYMBOL.name: SYMBOL
SYMBOL.comment: The symbol of the token / asset.

AMOUNT_DEPOSITED_UNADJUSTED.name: AMOUNT_DEPOSITED_UNADJUSTED
AMOUNT_DEPOSITED_UNADJUSTED.comment: The raw amount of the token being deposited into a Maker vault. Divide this through by POW(10, DECIMALS) to get the actual amount.

DECIMALS.name: DECIMALS
DECIMALS.comment: Divide amount by POW(10, DECIMALS) to convert raw amount to actual amount.

AMOUNT_DEPOSITED.name: AMOUNT_DEPOSITED
AMOUNT_DEPOSITED.comment: The amount of the token being deposited into a Maker vault.

_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.name: _INSERTED_TIMESTAMP
_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.comment: Time at which the record was inserted into the table.

_LOG_ID.name: _LOG_ID
_LOG_ID.comment: This is the primary key for this table. This is a concatenation of the transaction hash and the event index at which the event occurred. This field can be used within other event based tables such as ```fact_transfers``` & ```ez_token_transfers```.

metadata.name: EZ_LENDING
metadata.comment: This is a table that shows all the events on ethereum that are related to providing capital for lending and withdrawing capital

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block was produced.

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: Also known as block height. The block number, which indicates the length of the blockchain, increases after the addition of each new block.

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: Transaction hash is a unique 66-character identifier that is generated when a transaction is executed. This field will not be unique in this table, as a given transaction can include multiple events.

ACTION.name: ACTION
ACTION.comment:
The action that the user is taking.
 Deposit: user is depositing funds to be used for lending
 Withdraw: user has changed their mind and are no longer willing to lend, so they withdraw their asset

ASSET.name: ASSET
ASSET.comment: The address of the asset (token) that is being deposited/withdrawn, depending on the action

DEPOSITOR.name: DEPOSITOR
DEPOSITOR.comment: Its the address of the user who is depositing for lending or withdrawing, depending on the action.

LENDING_POOL_ADDRESS.name: LENDING_POOL_ADDRESS
LENDING_POOL_ADDRESS.comment: The address of the lending pool. For sushi this will be the address of the kashi pair.

AMOUNT.name: AMOUNT
AMOUNT.comment: The amount of the asset that the user is depositing or withdrawing, depending on the action.

AMOUNT_USD.name: AMOUNT_USD
AMOUNT_USD.comment: The amount of the asset that the user is depositing or withdrawing, depending on the action.

SYMBOL.name: SYMBOL
SYMBOL.comment: The symbol of the asset that is lent or withdrawn, depending on the action

_LOG_ID.name: _LOG_ID
_LOG_ID.comment: This is the primary key for this table. This is a concatenation of the transaction hash and the event index at which the event occurred. This field can be used within other event based tables such as ```fact_transfers``` & ```ez_token_transfers```.

metadata.name: EZ_NFT_SALES
metadata.comment: This table contains NFT events on the Ethereum blockchain. It currently supports sales on Opensea, Seaport, Larva Labs, LooksRare, Rarible, x2y2, Sudoswap, and NFTX. More data and exchanges will be added over time.

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: The block number at which the NFT event occurred.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The block timestamp at which the NFT event occurred.

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: The transaction hash for the NFT event. This is not necessarily unique in this table as a transaction may contain multiple NFT events.

EVENT_TYPE.name: EVENT_TYPE
EVENT_TYPE.comment: The type of NFT event in this transaction, either `sale`,  `bid_won` or `redeem`.

PLATFORM_ADDRESS.name: PLATFORM_ADDRESS
PLATFORM_ADDRESS.comment: The address of the exchange used for the transaction.

PLATFORM_NAME.name: PLATFORM_NAME
PLATFORM_NAME.comment: The name of the exchange used for the trade. Currently, the exchanges supported are `opensea`, `looksrare`, `larva labs`, `rarible`, `x2y2`, `sudoswap`, and `nftx`. More exchanges will be added over time.

PLATFORM_EXCHANGE_VERSION.name: PLATFORM_EXCHANGE_VERSION
PLATFORM_EXCHANGE_VERSION.comment: The version of the exchange contract used for the transaction.

SELLER_ADDRESS.name: SELLER_ADDRESS
SELLER_ADDRESS.comment: The address of the seller of the NFT in the transaction.

BUYER_ADDRESS.name: BUYER_ADDRESS
BUYER_ADDRESS.comment: The address of the buyer of the NFT in the transaction.

NFT_ADDRESS.name: NFT_ADDRESS
NFT_ADDRESS.comment: The contract address of the NFT.

PROJECT_NAME.name: PROJECT_NAME
PROJECT_NAME.comment: The name of the NFT project. This field, along with metadata, will be filled in over time.

ERC1155_VALUE.name: ERC1155_VALUE
ERC1155_VALUE.comment: If the NFT is an ERC-1155 contract, this field may be one or greater, representing the number of tokens.

TOKENID.name: TOKENID
TOKENID.comment: The token ID for this NFT contract.

TOKEN_METADATA.name: TOKEN_METADATA
TOKEN_METADATA.comment: The token metadata for this NFT. This may be blank for many NFTs. We are working to expand this field.

CURRENCY_SYMBOL.name: CURRENCY_SYMBOL
CURRENCY_SYMBOL.comment: The token symbol for this NFT event.

CURRENCY_ADDRESS.name: CURRENCY_ADDRESS
CURRENCY_ADDRESS.comment: The token contract address for this NFT event. This will be `ETH` for native ETH transactions.

PRICE.name: PRICE
PRICE.comment: The amount of the NFT event in the currency in which the transaction occurred, decimal adjusted where possible.

PRICE_USD.name: PRICE_USD
PRICE_USD.comment: The amount of the NFT event in US dollars. This will be null for tokens without a decimal adjustment or hourly price.

TOTAL_FEES.name: TOTAL_FEES
TOTAL_FEES.comment: The total amount of fees paid relating to the NFT purchase in the transaction currency. This includes royalty payments to creators and platform fees. Please note, this does not include the gas fee.

PLATFORM_FEE.name: PLATFORM_FEE
PLATFORM_FEE.comment: The decimal adjusted amount of fees paid to the platform for this NFT event in the transaction's currency. For Opensea, we assume a 2.5% fee on all marketplace purchases, per their docs. Private sales do not have platform or creator fees on Opensea.

CREATOR_FEE.name: CREATOR_FEE
CREATOR_FEE.comment: The decimal adjusted amount of fees paid to the NFT collection as royalty payments for this NFT event in the transaction's currency. For Opensea, this is the difference between the total fees paid and a 2.5% Opensea platform fee.

TOTAL_FEES_USD.name: TOTAL_FEES_USD
TOTAL_FEES_USD.comment: The total amount of fees paid relating to the NFT purchase in US dollars. This includes royalty payments to creators and platform fees. Please note, this does not include the gas fee.

PLATFORM_FEE_USD.name: PLATFORM_FEE_USD
PLATFORM_FEE_USD.comment: The amount of fees paid to the platform for this NFT event in US dollars. For Opensea, we assume a 2.5% fee on all marketplace purchases, per their docs. Private sales do not have platform or creator fees on Opensea.

CREATOR_FEE_USD.name: CREATOR_FEE_USD
CREATOR_FEE_USD.comment: The amount of fees paid to the NFT collection as royalty payments for this NFT event in US dollars. For Opensea, this is the difference between the total fees paid and a 2.5% Opensea platform fee.

TX_FEE.name: TX_FEE
TX_FEE.comment: The gas fee for this transaction in ETH.

TX_FEE_USD.name: TX_FEE_USD
TX_FEE_USD.comment: The gas fee for this transaction in US dollars.

ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS.name: ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS
ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS.comment: The from address of this transaction. In most cases, this is the NFT buyer. However, for some more complex transactions, it may not be the NFT buyer.

ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS.name: ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS
ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS.comment: The to address of this transaction. In most cases, this is the exchange contract. However, for some more complex NFT events, such as aggregate buys with tools such as Gem and Genie, this may not be the exchange address.

ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE.name: ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE
ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE.comment: The function signature of this transaction.

metadata.name: GOVERNANCE_VOTES
metadata.comment: A record of votes and vote choice selected on all Maker proposals.

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: Also known as block height. The block number, which indicates the length of the blockchain, increases after the addition of each new block.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block was produced.

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: Transaction hash is a unique 66-character identifier that is generated when a transaction is executed.

EVENT_INDEX.name: EVENT_INDEX
EVENT_INDEX.comment: An index signifying where an event occurred within a transaction.

VOTER.name: VOTER
VOTER.comment: The wallet address of the user or delegate voting on a governance proposal.

POLLING_CONTRACT.name: POLLING_CONTRACT
POLLING_CONTRACT.comment: The governance contract that is used to conduct the vote. In this table, all governance contracts are associated with Maker DAO.

VOTE_OPTION.name: VOTE_OPTION
VOTE_OPTION.comment: The vote option is how the user voted on the proposal.

PROPOSAL_ID.name: PROPOSAL_ID
PROPOSAL_ID.comment: An address that is associated with the proposal that the user is voting on.

_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.name: _INSERTED_TIMESTAMP
_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.comment: Time at which the record was inserted into the table.

_LOG_ID.name: _LOG_ID
_LOG_ID.comment: This is the primary key for this table. This is a concatenation of the transaction hash and the event index at which the event occurred. This field can be used within other event based tables such as ```fact_transfers``` & ```ez_token_transfers```.

metadata.name: EZ_BALANCE_DELTAS
metadata.comment:
This table contains the block level balance changes for both tokens (including ERC721s) and Native ETH on the Ethereum Blockchain for all wallets and contracts. If a token or Native ETH is moved, we will read the balance of the involved wallets at that block, and carry forward the previous balance into the current record. Symbol, name, and price are joined where possible. ERC721s are included. Data is currently read at the max daily block for wallets with activity. We plan to increase the granularity on this table to block level changes in the near term. 

Please note - the underlying data for this is large. If you want your query to run quickly, please use filters as much as possible. Using at least `block_timestamp::date` as a filter will lead to optimal query performance.

If you want to take this data and make it daily, you can do so with the query below. You must use a `block_timestamp::date` filter here at a minimum. Other filters will help query runtime. 

```sql
WITH base_table AS (
    SELECT
        block_timestamp :: DATE AS balance_date,
        CASE
            WHEN symbol = 'ETH' THEN 'ETH'
            ELSE contract_address
        END AS contract_address,
        user_address,
        symbol,
        current_bal
    FROM
        ethereum.core.ez_balance_diffs
    WHERE
        block_timestamp :: DATE >= '' --user input 
        AND user_address = '' --user input
        AND (
            contract_address = '' --user input
            OR symbol = 'ETH'
        )
),
all_days AS (
    SELECT
        date_day AS balance_date
    FROM
        ethereum.core.dim_dates
),
address_ranges AS (
    SELECT
        user_address,
        contract_address,
        symbol,
        MIN(
            balance_date :: DATE
        ) AS min_block_date,
        CURRENT_DATE() :: DATE AS max_block_date
    FROM
        base_table
    GROUP BY
        user_address,
        contract_address,
        symbol,
        max_block_date
),
all_dates AS (
    SELECT
        C.balance_date,
        A.user_address,
        A.contract_address,
        A.symbol
    FROM
        all_days C
        LEFT JOIN address_ranges A
        ON C.full_balance_date BETWEEN A.min_block_date
        AND A.max_block_date
    WHERE
        A.user_address IS NOT NULL
),
eth_balances AS (
    SELECT
        user_address,
        contract_address,
        balance_date,
        current_bal,
        TRUE AS daily_activity
    FROM
        base_table
),
balance_tmp AS (
    SELECT
        d.balance_date,
        d.user_address,
        d.contract_address,
        d.symbol,
        b.current_bal,
        b.daily_activity
    FROM
        all_dates d
        LEFT JOIN eth_balances b
        ON d.balance_date = b.balance_date
        AND d.user_address = b.user_address
        AND d.contract_address = b.contract_address
),
FINAL AS (
    SELECT
        balance_date,
        user_address,
        contract_address,
        symbol,
        LAST_VALUE(
            current_bal ignore nulls
        ) over(
            PARTITION BY user_address,
            contract_address
            ORDER BY
                balance_date ASC rows unbounded preceding
        ) AS balance,
        CASE
            WHEN daily_activity IS NULL THEN FALSE
            ELSE TRUE
        END AS daily_activity
    FROM
        balance_tmp
)
SELECT
    *
FROM
    FINAL
WHERE
    balance <> 0
ORDER BY
    balance_date DESC,
    contract_address
```

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: Block at which the balance was read (when the transfer occurred).

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: Block timestamp at which the balance was read (when the transfer occurred).

USER_ADDRESS.name: USER_ADDRESS
USER_ADDRESS.comment: The wallet address holding the tokens / ETH.

CONTRACT_ADDRESS.name: CONTRACT_ADDRESS
CONTRACT_ADDRESS.comment: The contract address of the token (null for ETH).

PREV_BAL_UNADJ.name: PREV_BAL_UNADJ
PREV_BAL_UNADJ.comment: The token or ETH balance from the previously recorded record for this wallet / token, without a decimal adjustment.

PREV_BAL.name: PREV_BAL
PREV_BAL.comment: The decimal adjusted token or ETH balance from the previously recorded record for this wallet and token.

PREV_BAL_USD.name: PREV_BAL_USD
PREV_BAL_USD.comment: Previously recorded balance in USD - this will be null for tokens without a decimal adjustment. Please note, the USD value is calculated at this block.

CURRENT_BAL_UNADJ.name: CURRENT_BAL_UNADJ
CURRENT_BAL_UNADJ.comment: The token or ETH balance at the current block number, without a decimal adjustment.

CURRENT_BAL.name: CURRENT_BAL
CURRENT_BAL.comment: The decimal adjusted token or ETH balance at the current block number.

CURRENT_BAL_USD.name: CURRENT_BAL_USD
CURRENT_BAL_USD.comment: The current balance in USD - this will be null for tokens without a decimal adjustment. Please note, the USD value is calculated at this block.

BAL_DELTA_USD.name: BAL_DELTA_USD
BAL_DELTA_USD.comment: The balance change in USD, will be null for tokens without a decimal.

SYMBOL.name: SYMBOL
SYMBOL.comment: The symbol of the token contract, or ETH.

TOKEN_NAME.name: TOKEN_NAME
TOKEN_NAME.comment: The name of the token contract, or Native ETH.

DECIMALS.name: DECIMALS
DECIMALS.comment: The decimals for the token contract.

HAS_DECIMAL.name: HAS_DECIMAL
HAS_DECIMAL.comment: Whether the token has a decimal or not, either TRUE or FALSE.

HAS_PRICE.name: HAS_PRICE
HAS_PRICE.comment: Whether the token has an hourly price or not, either TRUE or FALSE.

metadata.name: EZ_BORROWING
metadata.comment: This is a table that shows all the events on ethereum that are related to Borrowing or repaying the loan

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block was produced.

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: Also known as block height. The block number, which indicates the length of the blockchain, increases after the addition of each new block.

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: Transaction hash is a unique 66-character identifier that is generated when a transaction is executed. This field will not be unique in this table, as a given transaction can include multiple events.

ACTION.name: ACTION
ACTION.comment:
The action that the user is taking.
 Borrow: user is borrowing an asset
 Repay: user is repaying the asset that they have borrowed in a previous loan
 Add collateral: user is depositing collateral for their loan. This happens some times in the same transaction as the borrowing transaction and some times in a separate transaction. 
 Remove collateral: user is withdrawing collateral. This happens some times in the same transaction as the borrowing transaction and some times in a separate transaction.

LENDING_POOL_ADDRESS.name: LENDING_POOL_ADDRESS
LENDING_POOL_ADDRESS.comment: The address of the lending pool. For sushi this will be the address of the kashi pair.

ASSET.name: ASSET
ASSET.comment: The address of the asset/collateral token that is being borrowed/repayed/deposited etc. depending on the action

SYMBOL.name: SYMBOL
SYMBOL.comment: The symbol of the asset/collateral that is payed or received, depending on the action

AMOUNT.name: AMOUNT
AMOUNT.comment:
The meaning depends on the action:
Borrow: The amount of the asset that the user is borrowing or
Repay: The amount of the asset that the user is repaying
Add collateral: The amount of collateral that the user is depositing
Remove collateral: The amount of collateral that the user is withdrawing

AMOUNT_USD.name: AMOUNT_USD
AMOUNT_USD.comment:
The meaning depends on the action:
Borrow: The amount of the asset in USD that the user is borrowing or
Repay: The amount of the asset in USD that the user is repaying
Add collateral: The amount of collateral in USD that the user is depositing
Remove collateral: The amount of collateral in USD that the user is withdrawing

_LOG_ID.name: _LOG_ID
_LOG_ID.comment: This is the primary key for this table. This is a concatenation of the transaction hash and the event index at which the event occurred. This field can be used within other event based tables such as ```fact_transfers``` & ```ez_token_transfers```.

clustering_key.label: Clustering Key
clustering_key.description: The key used to cluster this table

row_count.description: An approximate count of rows in this table

bytes.label: Approximate Size
bytes.description: Approximate size of the table as reported by Snowflake

has_stats.label: Has Stats?
has_stats.description: Indicates whether there are statistics for this table

metadata.name: EZ_CURRENT_BALANCES
metadata.comment:
This table contains the current, non 0, balances for wallets on the Ethereum Blockchain. Symbol, name, and price are joined where possible. Prices are calculated as of the last activity date and as of the most recently recorded hourly price. ERC721s are included.

Please note - the underlying data for this is large. If you want your query to run quickly, please use filters as much as possible. Using at least `last_activity_block_timestamp::date` as a filter will lead to optimal query performance.

LAST_ACTIVITY_BLOCK.name: LAST_ACTIVITY_BLOCK
LAST_ACTIVITY_BLOCK.comment: The last block where this token was transferred by this address.

USER_ADDRESS.name: USER_ADDRESS
USER_ADDRESS.comment: The wallet address holding the tokens / ETH.

CONTRACT_ADDRESS.name: CONTRACT_ADDRESS
CONTRACT_ADDRESS.comment: The contract address of the token (null for ETH).

CURRENT_BAL_UNADJ.name: CURRENT_BAL_UNADJ
CURRENT_BAL_UNADJ.comment: The current token or ETH balance for this address, without a decimal adjustment.

CURRENT_BAL.name: CURRENT_BAL
CURRENT_BAL.comment: The decimal adjusted current token or ETH balance.

USD_VALUE_LAST_ACTIVITY.name: USD_VALUE_LAST_ACTIVITY
USD_VALUE_LAST_ACTIVITY.comment: The value of the tokens or ETH in USD, at the time the last token activity occurred. Will be null for tokens without a decimal.

USD_VALUE_NOW.name: USD_VALUE_NOW
USD_VALUE_NOW.comment: The value of the tokens or ETH in USD, as of the most recently recorded hourly price. Will be null for tokens without a decimal.

SYMBOL.name: SYMBOL
SYMBOL.comment: The symbol of the token contract, or ETH.

TOKEN_NAME.name: TOKEN_NAME
TOKEN_NAME.comment: The name of the token contract, or Native ETH.

DECIMALS.name: DECIMALS
DECIMALS.comment: The decimals for the token contract.

HAS_DECIMAL.name: HAS_DECIMAL
HAS_DECIMAL.comment: Whether the token has a decimal or not, either TRUE or FALSE.

HAS_PRICE.name: HAS_PRICE
HAS_PRICE.comment: Whether the token has an hourly price or not, either TRUE or FALSE.

LAST_RECORDED_PRICE.name: LAST_RECORDED_PRICE
LAST_RECORDED_PRICE.comment: The timestamp of the last hourly price recorded for this token.

metadata.name: FACT_TOKEN_TRANSFERS
metadata.comment: This table contains events on the Ethereum Blockchain with an event name of 'Transfer'. The contract address is the token transferred, and the raw amount field is the amount of tokens transferred. Please note this amount is not decimal adjusted. Decimal adjustments for a token address can be found in ```dim_contracts```. This table will not contain transfers of native ETH.

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: Also known as block height. The block number, which indicates the length of the blockchain, increases after the addition of each new block.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block was produced.

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: Transaction hash is a unique 66-character identifier that is generated when a transaction is executed. This will not be unique in this table as a transaction could include multiple transfer events.

ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE.name: ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE
ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE.comment: The function signature of this transaction.

ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS.name: ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS
ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS.comment: The from address at the transaction level.

ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS.name: ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS
ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS.comment: The to address at the transaction level.

CONTRACT_ADDRESS.name: CONTRACT_ADDRESS
CONTRACT_ADDRESS.comment: Contract address of the token being transferred.

FROM_ADDRESS.name: FROM_ADDRESS
FROM_ADDRESS.comment: The sending address of this transfer.

TO_ADDRESS.name: TO_ADDRESS
TO_ADDRESS.comment: The receiving address of this transfer. This can be a contract address.

RAW_AMOUNT.name: RAW_AMOUNT
RAW_AMOUNT.comment: The amount of tokens transferred. This value is not decimal adjusted.

_LOG_ID.name: _LOG_ID
_LOG_ID.comment: This is the primary key for this table. This is a concatenation of the transaction hash and the event index at which the transfer event occurred. This field can be used to find more details on the event within the ```fact_event_logs``` table.

metadata.name: EZ_SWAPS
metadata.comment:
This table will contain all swap events done on the Sushiswap platform in the ```fact_event_logs table```, joined along with the addresses of both tokens in the swap and the decimal adjusted prices.
Note: A rule has been put in place to null out the amount_USD if that number is too divergent between amount_in_USD and amount_out_usd. This can happen for swaps of less liquid tokens during very high fluctuation of price.

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: Also known as block height. The block number, which indicates the length of the blockchain, increases after the addition of each new block.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block was produced.

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: Transaction hash is a unique 66-character identifier that is generated when a transaction is executed. This field will not be unique in this table, as a given transaction can include multiple events.

ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE.name: ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE
ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE.comment: The function signature of this transaction.

ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS.name: ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS
ORIGIN_FROM_ADDRESS.comment: The from address at the transaction level.

ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS.name: ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS
ORIGIN_TO_ADDRESS.comment: The to address at the transaction level.

CONTRACT_ADDRESS.name: CONTRACT_ADDRESS
CONTRACT_ADDRESS.comment: The address interacted with for a given event.

EVENT_NAME.name: EVENT_NAME
EVENT_NAME.comment: The decoded event name for a given event.

AMOUNT_IN.name: AMOUNT_IN
AMOUNT_IN.comment: The amount of tokens put into the swap.

AMOUNT_OUT.name: AMOUNT_OUT
AMOUNT_OUT.comment: The amount of tokens taken out of or received from the swap.

SENDER.name: SENDER
SENDER.comment: The Router is the Sender in the swap function.

TX_TO.name: TX_TO
TX_TO.comment: The tx_to is the address who receives the swapped token. This corresponds to the "to" field in the swap function.

PLATFORM.name: PLATFORM
PLATFORM.comment: This field denotes which application the liquidity pool belongs to.

TOKEN_IN.name: TOKEN_IN
TOKEN_IN.comment: The address of the token sent for swap.

TOKEN_OUT.name: TOKEN_OUT
TOKEN_OUT.comment: The address of the token being swapped to.

SYMBOL_IN.name: SYMBOL_IN
SYMBOL_IN.comment: The symbol of the token sent for swap.

SYMBOL_OUT.name: SYMBOL_OUT
SYMBOL_OUT.comment: The symbol of the token being swapped to.

AMOUNT_IN_USD.name: AMOUNT_IN_USD
AMOUNT_IN_USD.comment: The amount of tokens put into the swap converted to USD using the price of the token.

AMOUNT_OUT_USD.name: AMOUNT_OUT_USD
AMOUNT_OUT_USD.comment: The amount of tokens taken out of or received from the swap converted to USD using the price of the token.

has_stats.description: Indicates whether there are statistics for this table

metadata.name: EZ_SWAPS
metadata.comment: All swaps that occur on V3 pools.

BLOCKCHAIN.name: BLOCKCHAIN
BLOCKCHAIN.comment: The blockchain on which transactions are being confirmed.

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: Also known as block height. The block number, which indicates the length of the blockchain, increases after the addition of each new block.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block was produced.

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: Transaction hash is a unique 66-character identifier that is generated when a transaction is executed. This will not be unique in this table as a transaction could include multiple transfer events.

POOL_ADDRESS.name: POOL_ADDRESS
POOL_ADDRESS.comment: The contract address of the pool

POOL_NAME.name: POOL_NAME
POOL_NAME.comment: The contract label/name of the pool

PRICE_1_0.name: PRICE_1_0
PRICE_1_0.comment: The amount of token1 per token0 that the swap occurred at

PRICE_0_1.name: PRICE_0_1
PRICE_0_1.comment: The amount of token0 per token1 that the swap occurred at

RECIPIENT.name: RECIPIENT
RECIPIENT.comment: The address that received the output of the swap

SENDER.name: SENDER
SENDER.comment: The address that initiated the swap call, and that received the callback

TICK.name: TICK
TICK.comment: The log base 1.0001 of the price of the pool after the swap

LIQUIDITY_ADJUSTED.name: LIQUIDITY_ADJUSTED
LIQUIDITY_ADJUSTED.comment: The liquidity of the pool, decimal adjusted.

EVENT_INDEX.name: EVENT_INDEX
EVENT_INDEX.comment: Log index pertains to the grouping of individual events together. Withing one log index there could be multiple events that take place and this would be the key to tie them together.

AMOUNT0_ADJUSTED.name: AMOUNT0_ADJUSTED
AMOUNT0_ADJUSTED.comment: The delta of the token0 balance of the pool, decimal adjusted.

AMOUNT1_ADJUSTED.name: AMOUNT1_ADJUSTED
AMOUNT1_ADJUSTED.comment: The delta of the token1 balance of the pool, decimal adjusted.

AMOUNT0_USD.name: AMOUNT0_USD

metadata.name: FACT_TRANSACTIONS
metadata.comment: This table contains transaction level data for the Ethereum Blockchain. Each transaction will have a unique transaction hash, along with transactions fees and an ETH value transferred when applicable. Transactions may be native ETH transfers or interactions with contract addresses. For more information, please see [The Ethereum Organization - Transactions](https://ethereum.org/en/developers/docs/transactions/)

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: Also known as block height. The block number, which indicates the length of the blockchain, increases after the addition of each new block.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block was produced.

BLOCK_HASH.name: BLOCK_HASH
BLOCK_HASH.comment: Block hash is a unique 66-character identifier that is generate when a block is produced.

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: Transaction hash is a unique 66-character identifier that is generated when a transaction is executed.

NONCE.name: NONCE
NONCE.comment: The number of transactions sent from a given address.

POSITION.name: POSITION
POSITION.comment: The position of the transaction within the block.

ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE.name: ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE
ORIGIN_FUNCTION_SIGNATURE.comment: The function signature of the contract call.

FROM_ADDRESS.name: FROM_ADDRESS
FROM_ADDRESS.comment: The sending address of this transaction.

TO_ADDRESS.name: TO_ADDRESS
TO_ADDRESS.comment: The receiving address of this transaction. This can be a contract address.

TX_FEE.name: TX_FEE
TX_FEE.comment: Amount paid to validate the transaction in Ether.

GAS_PRICE.name: GAS_PRICE
GAS_PRICE.comment: Cost per unit of gas in Gwei.

GAS_LIMIT.name: GAS_LIMIT
GAS_LIMIT.comment: Maximum amount of gas allocated for the transaction.

CUMULATIVE_GAS_USED.name: CUMULATIVE_GAS_USED
CUMULATIVE_GAS_USED.comment: The total amount of gas used when this transaction was executed in the block.

INPUT_DATA.name: INPUT_DATA
INPUT_DATA.comment: This column contains additional data for this transaction, and is commonly used as part of a contract interaction or as a message to the recipient.

TX_JSON.name: TX_JSON
TX_JSON.comment: This JSON column contains the transaction details, including event logs.

metadata.name: LIQUIDATIONS
metadata.comment: A record of all liquidations of Maker vaults. A liquidation occurs when the value of a vault's collateral falls below a required minimum level.

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: Also known as block height. The block number, which indicates the length of the blockchain, increases after the addition of each new block.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block was produced.

TX_HASH.name: TX_HASH
TX_HASH.comment: Transaction hash is a unique 66-character identifier that is generated when a transaction is executed.

COLLATERAL.name: COLLATERAL
COLLATERAL.comment: The address of the token / asset that is being used as collateral in the vault.

SYMBOL.name: SYMBOL
SYMBOL.comment: The symbol of the token / asset.

COLLATERAL_BALANCE_UNADJUSTED.name: COLLATERAL_BALANCE_UNADJUSTED
COLLATERAL_BALANCE_UNADJUSTED.comment: The raw amount of collateral in the vault at the time of liquidation. Divide through by POW(10, DECIMALS) to get the actual amount.

DECIMALS.name: DECIMALS
DECIMALS.comment: Divide amount by POW(10, DECIMALS) to convert raw amount to actual amount.

COLLATERAL_BALANCE.name: COLLATERAL_BALANCE
COLLATERAL_BALANCE.comment: The amount of collateral in the vault at the time of liquidation.

NORMALIZED_STABLECOIN_DEBT.name: NORMALIZED_STABLECOIN_DEBT
NORMALIZED_STABLECOIN_DEBT.comment: The vault's amount of debt as normalized with DAI.

VAULT.name: VAULT
VAULT.comment: Address associated with a Maker Vault. A vault is a tool that allows the owner to deposit collateral and generate DAI.

LIQUIDATED_WALLET.name: LIQUIDATED_WALLET
LIQUIDATED_WALLET.comment: The wallet address of the vault owner that is being liquidated.

LIQUIDATOR.name: LIQUIDATOR
LIQUIDATOR.comment: The wallet address of the liquidator, or the user who is purchasing vault collateral to cover the vault's debt.

AUCTION_ID.name: AUCTION_ID
AUCTION_ID.comment: An ID associated with the auction sale of the vault's collateral performed to cover the debt of the vault.

_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.name: _INSERTED_TIMESTAMP
_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.comment: Time at which the record was inserted into the table.

_LOG_ID.name: _LOG_ID
_LOG_ID.comment: This is the primary key for this table. This is a concatenation of the transaction hash and the event index at which the event occurred. This field can be used within other event based tables such as ```fact_transfers``` & ```ez_token_transfers```.

metadata.name: EZ_SNAPSHOT
metadata.comment: A table that contains all votes on Snapshot and information about the voting space and proposal. All data in this table is off chain.

ID.name: ID
ID.comment: A pseudo transaction hash assigned to all votes on snapshot.

PROPOSAL_ID.name: PROPOSAL_ID
PROPOSAL_ID.comment: An address that identifies the proposal being voted on.

VOTER.name: VOTER
VOTER.comment: The wallet address of the user that voted on a proposal.

VOTE_OPTION.name: VOTE_OPTION
VOTE_OPTION.comment: How the user voted on the proposal. Corresponds to the choices array.

VOTING_POWER.name: VOTING_POWER
VOTING_POWER.comment: The amount of voting power one holds is proportional to the amount of the token they hold.

VOTE_TIMESTAMP.name: VOTE_TIMESTAMP
VOTE_TIMESTAMP.comment: The time at which the vote was cast.

CHOICES.name: CHOICES
CHOICES.comment: An array containing the voting options on the proposal.

PROPOSAL_AUTHOR.name: PROPOSAL_AUTHOR
PROPOSAL_AUTHOR.comment: The address of the wallet that wrote the proposal.

PROPOSAL_TITLE.name: PROPOSAL_TITLE
PROPOSAL_TITLE.comment: The title or name of the proposal.

SPACE_ID.name: SPACE_ID
SPACE_ID.comment: A way to identify which group, or space, on Snapshot a proposal belongs to.

NETWORK.name: NETWORK
NETWORK.comment: The default network or blockchain used for the space.

DELAY.name: DELAY
DELAY.comment: The default number of hours of voting delay for the space. The voting delay is the time between proposal submission and the opening of voting.

QUORUM.name: QUORUM
QUORUM.comment: The minimum amount of voting power for a proposal to pass.

VOTING_PERIOD.name: VOTING_PERIOD
VOTING_PERIOD.comment: The default time in hours within a space for a proposal to be open for voting.

VOTING_TYPE.name: VOTING_TYPE
VOTING_TYPE.comment: The type of voting system used for this space. If this column is not null, the same voting system will be used for all proposals in this space.

PROPOSAL_START_TIME.name: PROPOSAL_START_TIME
PROPOSAL_START_TIME.comment: The time at which voting on the proposal begins.

PROPOSAL_END_TIME.name: PROPOSAL_END_TIME
PROPOSAL_END_TIME.comment: The time at which voting on the proposal ends.

metadata.name: FACT_BLOCKS
metadata.comment: This table contains block level data for the Ethereum Blockchain. This table can be used to analyze trends at a block level, for example gas fees vs. total transactions over time. For more information, please see [Etherscan Resources](https://etherscan.io/directory/Learning_Resources/Ethereum) or [The Ethereum Organization](https://ethereum.org/en/developers/docs/blocks/)

BLOCK_NUMBER.name: BLOCK_NUMBER
BLOCK_NUMBER.comment: Also known as block height. The block number, which indicates the length of the blockchain, increases after the addition of each new block.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block was produced.

NETWORK.name: NETWORK
NETWORK.comment: The network on the blockchain used by a transaction.

BLOCKCHAIN.name: BLOCKCHAIN
BLOCKCHAIN.comment: The blockchain on which transactions are being confirmed.

TX_COUNT.name: TX_COUNT
TX_COUNT.comment: Total number of transactions within a block.

DIFFICULTY.name: DIFFICULTY
DIFFICULTY.comment: The effort required to mine the block.

TOTAL_DIFFICULTY.name: TOTAL_DIFFICULTY
TOTAL_DIFFICULTY.comment: Total difficulty of the chain at a given block.

EXTRA_DATA.name: EXTRA_DATA
EXTRA_DATA.comment: Any data included by the miner for a given block.

GAS_LIMIT.name: GAS_LIMIT
GAS_LIMIT.comment: Total gas limit provided by all transactions in the block.

GAS_USED.name: GAS_USED
GAS_USED.comment: Total gas used in the block.

HASH.name: HASH
HASH.comment: The hash of the block header for a given block.

PARENT_HASH.name: PARENT_HASH
PARENT_HASH.comment: The hash of the block from which a given block is generated. Also known as the parent block.

MINER.name: MINER
MINER.comment: Miner who successfully added a given block to the blockchain.

NONCE.name: NONCE
NONCE.comment: Block nonce is a value used during mining to demonstrate proof of work for a given block.

RECEIPTS_ROOT.name: RECEIPTS_ROOT
RECEIPTS_ROOT.comment: The root of the state trie.

SHA3_UNCLES.name: SHA3_UNCLES
SHA3_UNCLES.comment: The mechanism which Ethereum Javascript RLP encodes an empty string.

SIZE.name: SIZE
SIZE.comment: Block size, which is determined by a given block's gas limit.

UNCLE_BLOCKS.name: UNCLE_BLOCKS
UNCLE_BLOCKS.comment: Uncle blocks occur when two blocks are mined and broadcasted at the same time, with the same block number. The block validated across the most nodes will be added to the primary chain, and the other one becomes an uncle block. Miners do receive rewards for uncle blocks.

BLOCK_HEADER_JSON.name: BLOCK_HEADER_JSON
BLOCK_HEADER_JSON.comment: This JSON column contains the block header details.
